body.description: Get ready for your next holiday with the Beach-stripes collection from IT Luggage. The 8-wheel spinner system will let you glide effortlessly on your next journey while the 4 different sizes means that you will always be prepared for every trip no matter how short or long. The leather look trim detailing gives the suitcase a very fashionable look which is easy to clean. The lightweight trolley system means you can pack more clothes without worrying about check-in weight restrictions while the unique base structure gives unparalleled strength and stability. The 8-wheel spinner system gives industry leading control. Travelling made fun with the Beach-stripes collection.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really cute, rolls great. Not sure how it will hold up in the harsh world of airline handling, but it’s inexpensive and holds a really good amount.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I've used this on four trips so far. It's held up through airport handling so far. The construction is kind of thin, but seems to be durable.The suitcase is VERY lightweight. And, it travels smoothly over every surface and doesn't get stuck in cracks. I've used name brand luggage that doesn't roll as easily.Even if it lasts only a year or two, I would still buy it again, due to price, weight and smooth rolling.I highly recommend.

reviews.reviewText: This 26" suitcase is a good size for me. It's easy to spot on the carousel and glides through the airport. Of course it got dirty, but it's luggage! The price was right, it holds what I need. Good deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I travelled for two month with this suitcase and was disappointed and frustrated with the way it functioned. It regularly toppled over. This happened whether or not there was a small item on top looped through the handle. I have had two previous IT suitcases and had never experienced this. Some others seem to experience this problem while others don’t.Also, tho less importantly, the suitcase got very dirty on the first plane ride.The good thing about the suitcase is, of course, that it is lightweight.Is there any recourse for this situation?
